obo:GO_0098794  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_5103  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1a: Immunocytochemical staining of cultured hippocampal neurons reveals that paralemmin-1 (PALM) is localized in patches along the plasma membrane. It is also detected in dendritic filopodia at 10 days in vitro (DIV 10) and spines in mature neurons (DIV26).\n\nFigure 1b,c: Hippocampal neurons were cotransfected at DIV 5 with RFP and either GFP, GFP-paralemmin-S, the short variant of paralemmin-1 lacking sequences encoded by exon 8 (GFP-PALM-S) or GFP-paralemmin-L, the long variant containing sequences encoded by exon 8 (GFP-PALM-L). Quantification of the number of filopodia/100 μm shows that expression of both paralemmin-1 splice variants increase filopodia number.\n\nFigure 1d,e: Quantification of the number of filopodia/100 μm shows paralemmin-1 knockdown diminishes the number of filopodia formed, and these effects can be rescued upon expression PALM Res.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Primary Neuronal Culture Preparation, Transfection, Treatments, and Immunocytochemistry - Neuronal cultures were prepared from hippocampal embryonic day 18/19 rats. ... For endogenous paralemmin-1 detection, rabbit anti-paralemmin-1 sera 2 and 10 were used (Kutzleb et al., 1998).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5103" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

